The paper deals with lower bounds for monotone arithmetic circuits, which are a topic in computational complexity theory. The most likely category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity), which deals with the study of the inherent difficulty of computational problems. The paper also involves the analysis of polynomials, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The study of circuits and their properties could also be relevant to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.SC (Symbolic Computation and Formal Verification).
